<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920303-0007</DOCNO><DOCID>920303-0007.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Kerr Glass Manufacturing Corp.:   Widened Losses Are Posted   For Fourth Quarter, Year</HL><DATE>03/03/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C6</SO><CO>   BLL KGM</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>CONTAINERS andamp; PACKAGING, BAGS, CANS, BOXES (CTR)EARNINGS (ERN)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)INDIANA (IND)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Kerr Glass Manufacturing Corp. posted widened losses forthe fourth quarter and 1991.   For the quarter, Los Angeles-based Kerr had a net loss of$4.1 million, or $1.17 a share, compared with a year-earlierloss of $1.7 million, or 52 cents a share. Sales fell 9.7% to$27.6 million from $30.6 million. The latest quarterreflected a $3 million loss, equal to 81 cents a share,related to the sale.</LP><TEXT>   For the full year, Kerr's loss widened to $2.6 million, or93 cents a share, from $1.3 million, or 57 cents a share.Sales fell 3.4% to $145.4 million from $150.4 million.   Kerr said the sale of its glass container business to BallCorp of Muncie, Ind., will enable it to focus on its plasticpackaging, home-canning supplies and other businesses. Thecompanies announced the completion of the sale yesterday.</TEXT></DOC>